cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.IT, cs.LO

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with automatic sequences and their properties, which are closely related to formal languages and automata theory.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the computation of characteristic functions for various sequences, which involves algorithmic techniques.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with combinatorial properties of words in automatic sequences.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the expressibility of certain properties in first-order logic, which is related to information theory.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper deals with the expressibility of properties in first-order logic for automatic sequences.
